 Several Nikkei board members have grown impatient with the <i>Financial Ti=
mes</i>=E2=80=99 economic performance and are pushing for consideration of =
a sale, according to three sources with knowledge of the matter. The Japane=
se holding firm bought the <i>FT </i>nearly a decade ago for =C2=A3844 mill=
ion, or $1.32 billion, but it has =E2=80=9Cnever really met expectations,=
=E2=80=9D one source with knowledge of the business said. (<i>FT
</i>spokespeople declined to comment.)<br/><br/>Obviously, there would be n=
o shortage of interested buyers on both sides of the Atlantic: <b>Jeff Bezo=
